      <hedline>
        <hl1>Windmill Stir</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Charles Komanoff letter on March 2 article contends opponents of wind-power project in Nantucket Sound are not environmentalists</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding '' A Wind Power Plan Stirs Debate in Massachusetts'' (Correspondent's Report, March 2): The opponents of a proposed wind-power project in Nantucket Sound should not be considered ''environmentalists.''</p>
        <p>For the most part, the windmill opponents are wealthy owners of beachfront property. What they are protecting is their pretty view. What the windmills will help protect is humanity and the Earth, by reducing our overuse of fossil fuels.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Regarding '' A Wind Power Plan Stirs Debate in Massachusetts'' (Correspondent's Report, March 2): The opponents of a proposed wind-power project in Nantucket Sound should not be considered ''environmentalists.''</p>
        <p>For the most part, the windmill opponents are wealthy owners of beachfront property. What they are protecting is their pretty view. What the windmills will help protect is humanity and the Earth, by reducing our overuse of fossil fuels.</p>
        <p>In this case, the real environmentalists are the wind-power developers.</p>
        <p>Charles Komanoff  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
